- cs.PF (Power and Energy): The paper is focused on the stability and frequency regulation of inverters, which are devices used in power and energy systems. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The use of capacitive inertia in inverters is a relatively new and emerging technology in the field of power electronics. 
- cs.EE (Electrical Engineering): The paper deals with the modeling, stability, and control of electrical power systems, which is a core topic in electrical engineering. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses numerical simulations to illustrate the effectiveness of the proposed method, which falls under the scope of computational engineering.
